(1834, 160948, '2012-08-03 02:13:36', '"We examined\na total of 65 cells and 50% (26 out of 52) of the\nVIP-immunoreactive cells in CA1 and 54% (seven\nout of 13) in the CA3 were shown to be positive for\ncalretinin. Interneurons co-localizing calretinin and\nVIP represented 37% of calretinin-containing cells in\nthe CAl and 11% in the CA3 subfield. In CA3, none\nof the double-labelled cells belonged to the spiny type\nof calretinin-positive neurons. (14)"', 'p 308 left', 'data'),
