(1993, 150114, '2012-08-03 02:13:38', '"In the hippocampus, basket, axo-axonic, bistratified, and oriens-lacunosum moleculare (O-LM) cells innervate pyramidal cells mainly on the soma, axon initial segment, and dendrites in stratum radiatum/oriens or lacunosum moleculare, respectively, and all these cells express parvalbumin (PV). The weak expression of PV by O-LM cells was reported both from a small sample of in vivo recorded cells (Klausberger et al., 2003) and a population survey (Ferraguti et al., 2004)."', 'p 9782, left mid', 'data'),
